thread.title: German Coalition Deal Evokes Relief and Anxiety in Europe

author: Simon Nixon
title: German Coalition Deal Evokes Relief and Anxiety in Europe
text:
The news that German Chancellor Angela Merkel has at last succeeded in negotiating a new coalition agreement with the Social Democrats will of course be greeted with relief across Europe. Assuming the deal is ratified by a ballot of SPD members—by no means assured—it will bring an end to five months of uncertainty over Germany’s political stability.
Nonetheless, the news will also induce a degree of anxiety.
